elvoke (0.5) unstable; urgency=low

  * Use $XDG_DATA_HOME/elvoke/ (with fallback to ~/.local/share/elvoke/)
    as default stamp directory.
    https://github.com/jwilk/elvoke/issues/1
  * Deprecate ~/.elvoke/ and $XDG_CACHE_HOME/elvoke/ (with fallback to
    ~/.cache/elvoke/) as stamp directories.
  * Don't the require HOME environment variable to be set.
  * Fix typos in the manual page.

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Thu, 08 Feb 2024 13:06:05 +0100

elvoke (0.4) unstable; urgency=low

  * Require Perl v5.10 (or a later version).
  * Don't require File::BaseDir.
  * Don't chdir to the stamp directory.
  * Create the stamp directory only when needed.
  * Fix handling exit status of children killed by signals.
  * Remove undocumented --filename (alias for -f/--file).
  * Add the test suite.
  * Make --version print Perl version.
  * Improve the build system:
    + Add checks against BSD make.
    + Add “test” and “test-installed” targets.
  * Improve documentation:
    + Add README.
    + Clarify synopsis in the manual page.
    + Abridge the --help message.
    + Improve the manual page:
      - Rephrase --file description.
      - Rephrase FILES section.
      - Rephrase --debug description.
      - Rephrase --help/--version descriptions.
  * Improve error handling.

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Fri, 20 Dec 2019 16:19:48 +0100

elvoke (0.3) unstable; urgency=low

  * Change the license to Expat.
  * Follow the XDG Base Directory specification.
  * Add Makefile.
  * Use /usr/bin/env in shebang.
  * Improve the manual page, as per man-pages(7) recommendations:
    + Fix syntax in the NAME section.
    + Remove the AUTHOR and COPYRIGHT sections.
    + Add the DESCRIPTION section.
    + Improve wording.
    + Improve formatting.
  * Make --version and --help exit with code 0.
  * Simplify --version output.
  * Fix typo in a debug message.
  * Explicitly remove current working directory from the module search path.
    Work-around for CVE-2016-1238.
  * Remove Debian packaging.

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Fri, 29 Sep 2017 22:19:53 +0200

